---
import IntroductionIcon from "../../icons/IntroductionIcon.astro";
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout>
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-8 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-white">
    <section
      class="text-center mb-12 p-8 bg-linear-to-r from-cyan-950/40 to-blue-950/40 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/20 backdrop-blur-sm"
    >
      <div class="flex items-center justify-center mb-4 gap-3">
        <IntroductionIcon class="size-10 text-cyan-400" />
        <h1
          class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-3 bg-linear-to-r from-cyan-400 to-blue-400 bg-clip-text"
        >
          Introduction
        </h1>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg text-body/80">
        Learn the fundamentals of building modern web applications with Astro
        and Tailwind CSS
      </p>
    </section>

    <section
      class="mb-12 p-6 bg-neutral-secondary-soft rounded-lg border border-default"
    >
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">What is Astro?</h2>
      <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
        Astro is a modern web framework designed for building fast,
        content-focused websites. It combines the best of static site generation
        with the flexibility of dynamic components, allowing you to create
        incredibly performant web applications with minimal JavaScript overhead.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-6">
        <div class="p-4 bg-cyan-950/20 rounded-lg border border-cyan-500/30">
          <h3 class="text-cyan-300 font-bold mb-2">‚ö° Performance First</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-body/80">
            Sends minimal JavaScript to the browser, resulting in lightning-fast
            load times and better user experience.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 bg-blue-950/20 rounded-lg border border-blue-500/30">
          <h3 class="text-blue-300 font-bold mb-2">üîß Islands Architecture</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-body/80">
            Load interactive components only when needed, keeping your pages
            lightweight and responsive.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      class="mb-12 p-6 bg-neutral-secondary-soft rounded-lg border border-default"
    >
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">What is Tailwind CSS?</h2>
      <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
        Tailwind CSS is a utility-first CSS framework that empowers you to build
        modern designs without ever leaving your HTML. Instead of relying on
        pre-made components, Tailwind provides low-level utility classes that
        let you construct custom designs with precision and consistency.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-6">
        <div class="p-4 bg-cyan-950/20 rounded-lg border border-cyan-500/30">
          <h3 class="text-cyan-300 font-bold mb-2">üé® Design System</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-body/80">
            A comprehensive set of colors, spacing, typography, and more that
            ensures visual consistency across your project.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 bg-blue-950/20 rounded-lg border border-blue-500/30">
          <h3 class="text-blue-300 font-bold mb-2">‚ú® Rapid Development</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-body/80">
            Style your components directly in markup, accelerating development
            and reducing context switching.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      class="mb-12 p-6 bg-neutral-secondary-soft rounded-lg border border-default"
    >
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
        Why Astro + Tailwind CSS?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
        Combining Astro with Tailwind CSS creates a powerful and efficient
        development experience. Astro handles the architecture and performance
        optimization, while Tailwind CSS provides the styling tools to create
        beautiful, responsive interfaces.
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-3 mt-6">
        <div
          class="flex items-start gap-4 p-4 bg-cyan-950/20 rounded-lg border border-cyan-500/30"
        >
          <span class="text-cyan-400 font-bold text-lg mt-1">‚úì</span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-white font-semibold">Ship less JavaScript</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-body/80">
              Astro's minimal JavaScript approach pairs perfectly with
              Tailwind's class-based styling
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          class="flex items-start gap-4 p-4 bg-blue-950/20 rounded-lg border border-blue-500/30"
        >
          <span class="text-blue-400 font-bold text-lg mt-1">‚úì</span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-white font-semibold">Faster development workflow</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-body/80">
              Build complete, styled components quickly without context
              switching between HTML and CSS files
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          class="flex items-start gap-4 p-4 bg-purple-950/20 rounded-lg border border-purple-500/30"
        >
          <span class="text-purple-400 font-bold text-lg mt-1">‚úì</span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-white font-semibold">Excellent scalability</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-body/80">
              Both frameworks are designed to scale from small projects to
              large-scale applications
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      class="mb-12 p-6 bg-neutral-secondary-soft rounded-lg border border-default"
    >
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">What You'll Learn</h2>
      <p class="text-body/80 mb-6">
        This documentation provides comprehensive guides to help you master both
        Astro and Tailwind CSS:
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div
          class="p-4 bg-black/20 rounded-lg border border-gray-700 hover:border-cyan-500/50 transition-all"
        >
          <h3 class="text-cyan-300 font-bold mb-2">üöÄ Getting Started</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-body/80">
            Installation instructions and initial setup to get your project
            running in minutes
          </p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="p-4 bg-black/20 rounded-lg border border-gray-700 hover:border-cyan-500/50 transition-all"
        >
          <h3 class="text-blue-300 font-bold mb-2">üìö Core Concepts</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-body/80">
            Understand Astro's routing, layouts, components, islands
            architecture, and content collections
          </p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="p-4 bg-black/20 rounded-lg border border-gray-700 hover:border-cyan-500/50 transition-all"
        >
          <h3 class="text-purple-300 font-bold mb-2">
            üé® Styling with Tailwind
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-body/80">
            Master responsive design, colors, spacing, typography, dark mode and
            advanced configuration
          </p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="p-4 bg-black/20 rounded-lg border border-gray-700 hover:border-cyan-500/50 transition-all"
        >
          <h3 class="text-green-300 font-bold mb-2">‚öôÔ∏è Best Practices</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-body/80">
            Professional patterns and techniques for building scalable,
            maintainable web applications
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      class="p-6 bg-linear-to-r from-cyan-950/30 to-blue-950/30 rounded-lg border border-cyan-500/30"
    >
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Ready to Begin?</h2>
      <p class="text-body/80 mb-6">
        If you're new to either Astro or Tailwind CSS, we recommend starting
        with the Installation guide to set up your first project. If you already
        have experience with these tools, feel free to jump directly to the
        sections that interest you most.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
        <a
          href="/docs/installation/"
          class="inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-cyan-500 hover:bg-cyan-600 text-white font-bold rounded-lg transition-colors"
        >
          Installation Guide ‚Üí
        </a>
        <a
          href="/docs/quick-start/"
          class="inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-blue-500/30 hover:bg-blue-500/50 text-blue-200 font-bold rounded-lg border border-blue-500/50 transition-colors"
        >
          Quick Start ‚Üí
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
